# Package.json Guidelines

Each module in this project has its own `package.json` with specific dependencies for learning purposes.

## Common Dependencies

### Webpack Ecosystem
- `webpack`: Core bundler
- `webpack-bundle-analyzer`: Bundle size analysis
- `terser-webpack-plugin`: JavaScript minification
- `babel-loader`: Babel integration
- `thread-loader`: Parallel processing

### Build Tools
- `rollup`: Alternative bundler
- `@babel/core`, `@babel/preset-env`: JavaScript transpilation
- `@swc/core`, `swc-loader`: Fast JavaScript compiler

### Performance Tools
- `speed-measure-webpack-plugin`: Build time measurement
- `webpack-bundle-analyzer`: Bundle visualization

## Module-Specific Dependencies

- **build-volume/**: Bundle analysis tools
- **rollup/**: Rollup-specific plugins
- **webpack-build-proformance/**: Performance comparison tools
- **json-loader/**: Custom loader development

## Scripts

Most modules don't have npm scripts defined. Use `node build.js` to run webpack configurations directly.

## Type Field

- `"type": "commonjs"` - Default for most modules
- `"type": "module"` - For ESM-only modules
- Check individual modules for their specific configuration